div.p: Patterns in galling and predation rates with latitude through the U.K. There were no significant geographical trends from the south to the north of the country in A. galling rates (including a squared term for northerliness; F 2,5 = 5.06, p = 0.063) or B. predation rates (F 1,6 = 0.69, p = 0.44).
